                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2691: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-09T12:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1922—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 9—9:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chinese Eastern Railway officials state that meeting of shareholders scheduled
                    Peking this fall indefinitely postponed because Chang Tso-lin objected on the
                    ground that the railway being in Manchuria is under his sole jurisdiction.
                    Matter considered grave. I believe only some international organ like Technical
                    Board attached to railway can prevent it from being made plaything of Chinese
                    militarists. Department has been informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
